From cff0d6daea403baa71a379b447e73183508c05d8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Carter Chen <carterchan50@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Apr 2026 07:04:02 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 06/13] brcmfmac: add sim_sdio.c bus shim + BRCMF_SIM_VAL debug
 level
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Implement the CONFIG_BRCMFMAC_HWSIM_SDIO bus shim (sim_sdio.c):

Platform lifecycle:
- brcmf_sim_sdio_register(): creates platform_device + registers driver
- sim_sdio_probe(): full probe flow with 8-step sequence:
  1. symbol_get(brcmf_hwsim_get_ops) → IPC bootstrap
  2. Register callbacks BEFORE fw_download (M12)
  3. Allocate brcmf_bus, chip=0xFFFF, proto=BCDC, fwvid=WCC
  4. dev_set_drvdata() BEFORE brcmf_alloc (D8)
  5. hwsim fw_download (simulated FW ready)
  6. brcmf_get_module_param() (D6)
  7. brcmf_alloc() (wiphy creation)
  8. brcmf_attach() (wlan0 created, BCDC proto attached)

Bus operations:
- stop: mandatory (DR-02, no NULL guard in bus.h)
- txctl/rxctl: synchronous via completion, rxctl returns byte count (D10)
- txdata: forwards to hwsim, then txcomplete (D1)
- get_blob: returns -ENOENT for all types (E1, mandatory)

Teardown protocol (B5/D14/DR-06):
- shutting_down → detach → brcmf_detach + brcmf_free →
  release_module_param → symbol_put

Also fix sim_bus_if.h tx_data doc: shim retains skb ownership, hwsim
must clone if it needs the data after tx_data returns.

Also add BRCMF_SIM_VAL (0x00200000) debug level to debug.h.

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
